---
const included = [
  "Monthly priority plan",
  "Technical SEO watchlist",
  "Search Console and analytics review",
  "Content and internal-link opportunities",
  "Website improvement notes",
  "Provider/account ownership notes",
  "Implementation support",
  "Plain-English reporting",
  "Next-step recommendations",
  "Documentation trail",
];
---

<section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#090a08] text-cream">
  <div
    class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(120deg,rgba(212,160,67,0.16),transparent_30%),radial-gradient(circle_at_82%_28%,rgba(212,160,67,0.16),transparent_26%)]"
  >
  </div>
  <div
    class="relative mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-10 px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 md:py-24 lg:grid-cols-[0.86fr_1.14fr] lg:items-center"
  >
    <div>
      <p
        class="text-sm font-extrabold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-honey-bright"
      >
        Monthly Growth Support
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black leading-tight text-cream md:text-5xl">
        Monthly support for the work that never stays fixed by itself.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-cream/78">
        SEO, content, analytics, and websites drift. Pages age. Reports get
        weird. Providers change things. Search behavior shifts. Monthly Growth
        Support keeps the system watched, prioritized, and documented.
      </p>
      <p
        class="mt-5 border-l-2 border-honey pl-4 text-base leading-7 text-cream/76"
      >
        Because Boho runs lean, monthly support can stay focused on actual work:
        monitoring, fixes, documentation, and next-step decisions.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/services/monthly-growth-retainer/"
          >Build the monthly system</a
        >
        <a
          class="btn border-honey/45 bg-transparent text-cream hover:border-honey hover:bg-honey/10 hover:text-cream"
          href="/services/seo-growth-audit/"
        >
          Start with an audit first
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-honey/25 bg-white/5 p-5 shadow-2xl">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-extrabold text-honey-bright">
        Monthly support includes
      </h3>
      <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {
          included.map((item) => (
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-honey/20 bg-black/20 px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-cream/84">
              {item}
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
